   RowBox[{"system", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"ampType", " ", "->", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{"a", ",", "s"}], "}"}], "/", 
        RowBox[{"{", "A", "}"}]}], " ", "OR", " ", "amp2Type"}], " ", "->", 
      " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", ",", "\[CapitalSigma]"}], "}"}], "/", 
       RowBox[{"{", "A", "}"}]}]}]}], ",", "..."}], "]"}]], "InlineCode",
  ExpressionUUID->"6aa273aa-0561-2e4c-9221-1f1c950dce28"],
 " function to format and extract the ASR/A2SR matrices and amplitude \
vector(s). Only one of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "ampType"], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "09d8feac-1a60-9c48-ac4e-86f11b9ffd7d"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "amp2Type"], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "5c254232-cf44-3946-883a-6bca0588ce80"],
 " should be specified, and only one of ASRs or A2SRs can be \
printed/extracted with this function.\n\nThe ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "printSRs"], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "b49676b4-3aeb-bf48-ab46-3850c7ce5bc8"],
 " function outputs a matrix or list of matrices corresponding to the \
specified orders of breaking. Use the option ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"b", " ", "->", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"All", "/", "Real"}], "/", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"min", ",", "max", ",", 
      RowBox[{"increment", "=", "1"}]}], "}"}]}]}]], "InlineCode",
  ExpressionUUID->"2b684c8f-06eb-404d-950e-e4c187aafbf6"],
 " to select the order(s) of the matrices to manipulate. If ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "b"], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->"0ba7dfa4-0fc8-3946-af9b-cc3648de3a2d"],
 " is set to a single number, the function outputs a single matrix. If ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "b"], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->"27599708-66c1-5f42-8aa2-84f0d334d3b2"],
 " is set to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "All"], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->"9a52a1ce-360b-7f4b-a2e3-e862477009f4"],
 " or a range, the function outputs a list of matrices corresponding to those \
orders of breaking.\n\nThe function also adds a vector, or a pair of vectors, \
of formatted amplitudes to the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "system"], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "185362c3-f7ed-464d-b643-64bd9869c1ce"],
 " association that can be accessed via ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"system", "[", 
   RowBox[{"[", "\"\<Amp vector\>\"", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineCode",
  ExpressionUUID->"088f1ca1-56e5-3548-b494-ca25bd29c2a1"],
 ". The amplitude or amplitude-squared basis and formatting options will \
determine the formatting of the amplitude vector(s).  If ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ampType", " ", "->", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"a", ",", "s"}], "}"}]}]], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "b75c781e-03d8-964b-8205-a020a67bf2e2"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"system", "[", 
   RowBox[{"[", "\"\<Amp vector\>\"", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineCode",
  ExpressionUUID->"e0d5f711-86ff-7942-ab40-3505f8c68a38"],
 " is a list ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"a", " ", "vector"}], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"s", " ", "vector"}]}], "}"}]], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "b2403c5b-5bc3-0f47-b92a-39638ff50305"],
 " containing two vectors, one of formatted a-type amplitudes and one of \
formatted s-type amplitudes; the same applies for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"amp2Type", " ", "->", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", ",", "\[CapitalSigma]"}], "}"}]}]], 
  "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->"34626a29-7005-8e4f-a4b1-6f9d8cff8d2d"],
 " with \[CapitalDelta]/\[CapitalSigma]-type amplitudes-squared. If ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ampType", " ", "->", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", "A", "}"}]}]], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "37f0d9ee-ff1e-854f-a38e-44252c9487e9"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"system", "[", 
   RowBox[{"[", "\"\<Amp vector\>\"", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineCode",
  ExpressionUUID->"3c8a9cd1-76a6-dc45-bd1c-9de3852c09cd"],
 " is a single formatted A-type amplitudes vector, and likewise for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"amp2Type", " ", "->", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", "A", "}"}]}]], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "973c8a1f-9646-bb49-a8cf-5962f0c8c92c"],
 ". Make sure to use a and \[CapitalDelta] (s and \[CapitalSigma]) vectors \
with even (odd) b sum rule matrices.\n\nIn this example, we generate a system \
and select its b = 1 ASR matrix (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"b", " ", "->", " ", "1"}]], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "79a644db-7ca7-4c4e-88ba-33be50ba0439"],
 ") for manipulation with A-type amplitudes (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ampType", " ", "->", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", "A", "}"}]}]], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "651e283e-6591-4b46-aa16-41c2273ec5b3"],
 ")."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9669587454157104`*^9, 3.966958813429323*^9}, {
